
CSRF happens when a malicious website/application/link tricks you into performing 
a unwanted action on a website where you are already logedin.


Simple Example:
You are logged into your bank account.
You visit a malicious website.
The malicious website sends a request to your bank (like transferring money) using your login session.
The bank thinks you made the request and performs the action.

Minigations :
Use Anti-CSRF Tokens
SameSite Cookies
Check Referer/Origin Headers
